; Regression test for GitHub issue #1869:
; getquote is called with an empty second argument when --market is used
; without --exchange, even though a price history entry exists that
; implies a concrete exchange commodity.
;
; When a commodity (BTC) has a price history entry denominated in a known
; currency ($), the download script should be invoked as:
;   getquote BTC $
; not as:
;   getquote BTC ''
;
; The mock script exits 1 if called with an empty exchange commodity ($2),
; which would leave BTC valued at the stale P-directive price.  With the
; fix, getquote receives '$' as $2, returns a fresh $40000 quote, and the
; balance reflects that updated price.
P 2024/01/01 BTC $3.00

2024/06/01 Bitcoin Mining
    Assets:BTC    1 BTC
    Income:Mining

test bal --market --download --getquote $sourcepath/test/scripts/mock-getquote-with-exchange.sh
           $40000.00  Assets:BTC
          $-40000.00  Income:Mining
--------------------
                   0
end test
